We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

snippet.title: Final Destination Bloodlines | Official Teaser Trailer
snippet.description:
If you screw with Death's plans, things can get very... messy. #FinalDestination #Bloodlines - only in theaters and IMAX May 16. #FilmedforIMAX

The newest chapter in New Line Cinema‚Äôs bloody successful franchise takes audiences back to the very beginning of Death‚Äôs twisted sense of justice‚Äî‚ÄúFinal Destination Bloodlines.‚Äù

Plagued by a violent recurring nightmare, college student Stefanie heads home to track down the one person who might be able to break the cycle and save her family from the grisly demise that inevitably awaits them all.
‚ÄúFinal Destination Bloodlines‚Äù stars Kaitlyn Santa Juana, Teo Briones, Richard Harmon, Owen Patrick Joyner, Rya Kihlstedt, Anna Lore, with Brec Bassinger, and Tony Todd.

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

The journey of a NEET aspirant is anything but easy, especially in a place like Kota, where thousands of students arrive every year with the AIIMS dream in their eyes. The medical entrance exam is one of the toughest battles, and the pressure to succeed feels unrelenting. Whether it's the last-minute revision before an important mock test, the endless coaching classes, or the library hours spent perfecting mnemonics for tricky concepts, every day is a new challenge. Hostel struggles become part of life‚Äîlearning to survive on late-night studies, chai breaks, and study groups that sometimes turn into therapy sessions.

For many students, the fear of failure looms large, especially with family expectations riding on their shoulders. Some come from small towns where becoming a future doctor is not just a personal goal but a family dream. The burden of competitive exams pushes students to their limits, testing their self-discipline and goal-oriented mindset. With every exam stress episode, the thought lingers‚Äîwill she make it? Is this the make-or-break moment?

In Kota, friendships are forged in the midst of sleepless nights, where friendship goals mean helping each other with topper mindset strategies and notes that can make or break a rank. Some students rely on their teacher‚Äôs pet status to get extra guidance, while others push themselves with a never give up attitude. The road to success is full of sacrifices‚Äîmissing family events, skipping social outings, and putting every ounce of energy into the hustle for the dream.

But this journey isn't just about studies. It's also about self-discovery, about realizing that hard work pays off only when paired with determination. Some students, like Bhagyashree, come to Kota with one shot at the dream, hoping that against all odds, their efforts will land them a seat in their dream MBBS journey. Others, like Saroj, have to balance dreams vs. reality, questioning whether their life-changing decision to come to Kota will ultimately lead them to success or if they‚Äôll be forced to take a different path.

From competitive exams to emotional breakdowns, from study struggles to moments of inspiration from mentors, every student here is fighting their own battle. Some thrive under the toughest pressure, while others seek motivation from their future doctor vision. But one thing remains true‚Äîthis medical entrance exam isn‚Äôt just about cracking a test; it‚Äôs about proving to yourself that you have what it takes to push through the hardest days and emerge stronger. Will they find their turning point, or will the weight of expectations take them somewhere they never expected?

This is the world of Medical Dreams‚Äîwhere passion meets perseverance, where success is fought for every single day, and where a single exam has the power to change lives forever. üöÄ

Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman presented her 8th Union Budget to the Parliament on 1st February 2025. The Budget covered different proposals for the Indian Economy.
In this video, Abhi and Niyu have covered important points from the Budget proposals, explained how the new tax slabs and rebate works, and explain how the Union Budget works. 

Here are some of the important proposals mentioned in the Budget:
* Nuclear Energy Mission
* Support to Footwear Industry (both leather and non leather)
* Makhana Board for Bihar
* Support to Make in India Toys
* Shipbuilding Financial Assistance Policy
* Policy to procure pulses directly from farmers on contract farming basis
* Modified UDAN scheme
* National Repository of Indian Knowledge books
* Bharat TRADENET
* High Level Committee for non financial sector regulatory reforms

Sources: 
Economic Survey: https://www.indiabudget.gov.in/economicsurvey/
Budget: https://www.indiabudget.gov.in/

snippet.title: Samsung is holding back, and I have proof! - Galaxy S25 Ultra Teardown
snippet.description:
Samsung is intentionally holding back the S25 Ultra - The S-pen slot looks like it has a charger - but the S-Pen itself has no battery! Reveal the secrets on your own phone HERE: https://www.dbrand.com/teardown The Samsung S25 Ultra used to be the king of Android smartphones. The Galaxy series would showcase the best that Android hardware had to offer. But with Samsung removing the SD card slot - taking away the batter inside the S-Pen... what else is there really to show off? Lets hope Samsung is prepping for an epic 2026 - or better yet - 2027.

snippet.title: School Ka Sports Day | Take A Break
snippet.description:
Ah, School Ka Sports Day‚Äîthe one day when even the laziest kids suddenly become athletes (at least in spirit)! üòú
In this hilarious sketch, we take you back to those unforgettable moments of school sports day, filled with awkward races, overenthusiastic teachers, biased referees, and parents acting like it‚Äôs the Olympics! üèÖ From kids faking injuries to avoid running, to the epic rivalry in the lemon-and-spoon race, we've captured it all in the most relatable way possible.
Share with your your school buddies and relive the madness together! üéΩü§£

snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Click here to watch NEW Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSxhJ6UCi6tgujD-FsAy0sw

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada

Gurucharan Singh/ Balwinder Suri as Roshan Singh Harjeet Singh Sodhi
Jennifer Mistry Bansiwal as Roshan Kaur Roshan Singh Sodhi

snippet.title: Saraswati Vandana | Shreya Ghoshal
snippet.description:
Shreya Ghoshal embarks on a new musical journey with devotion at its heart, beginning with a Saraswati Vandana‚Äîa sacred ode to the goddess of wisdom, music, and the arts. This newly composed hymn beautifully captures the essence of Ma Saraswati‚Äôs grace, symbolising the purity of mind, intellectual and spiritual enlightenment and creativity. Enriched by the ethereal voice of Shreya Ghoshal, whose pristine vocal texture brings unmatched beauty, the melody flows like a sacred offering, uplifting the soul and invoking the goddess‚Äôs blessings. Her vocals seamlessly weave into the poignant notes of Sarod and the lush choral arrangements. This musical offering is an invitation to immerse in the profound peace and inspiration that Ma Saraswati personifies.

Singer - Shreya Ghoshal

Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.
